LDG_DEBUG(3)                  LDG Call                    LDG_DEBUG(3)


NAME
    ldg_debug - debug a LDG library

SYNOPSIS
    int ldg_debug( char *fmt, ...);

PARAMETERS
        fmt : a string format like printf()

DESCRIPTION
    This function writes a message into  a log file. The complet  path
    of the log file is specified by the environ variable LDG_DEBUG. If 
    this variable is not defined, the function is unactived. If the 
    string begin by a '[' character , the string will be displayed in 
    a GEM alert box instead of be written in a log file.  Otherwise
    this function has the same usage than the printf() function.


